@startuml constraint_enforcement
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundCorner 10

title **Role Enforcement — 5 Layers of Agent Constraints**

skinparam rectangle {
  FontColor #1A1A1A
}

rectangle "**Layer 1: System Prompts** (Soft Constraint)" as L1 #E3F2FD {
  note right
    Defines role, responsibilities,
    and explicit restrictions.
    ----
    //Example: "You are the Market Researcher.//
    //You CANNOT do financial analysis.//
    //You CANNOT write the final report."//
    ----
    **Enforcement:** LLM instruction following
    **Strength:** Soft — can be bypassed
  end note
}

rectangle "**Layer 2: Tool Restrictions** (Hard Constraint)" as L2 #E8F5E9 {
  note right
    Each agent only has access to
    specific tool functions.
    ----
    //Market Researcher: search_web(), read_document()//
    //Financial Analyst: calculate(), create_projection()//
    //Cannot call tools outside their set//
    ----
    **Enforcement:** API-level tool filtering
    **Strength:** Hard — physically impossible
  end note
}

rectangle "**Layer 3: Output Schemas** (Hard Constraint)" as L3 #FFF3E0 {
  note right
    Each agent must respond in a
    specific JSON format.
    ----
    //Market Researcher → MarketAnalysis schema//
    //Financial Analyst → FinancialAnalysis schema//
    //Rejected if schema validation fails//
    ----
    **Enforcement:** Pydantic model validation
    **Strength:** Hard — invalid output rejected
  end note
}

rectangle "**Layer 4: Orchestrator Routing** (Hard Constraint)" as L4 #F3E5F5 {
  note right
    Central orchestrator controls data flow.
    Each agent only sees relevant data.
    ----
    //Market Researcher never sees financial data//
    //Risk Analyst never sees market research tools//
    //Pure Python logic — no LLM involved//
    ----
    **Enforcement:** Code-level data isolation
    **Strength:** Hard — data never exposed
  end note
}

rectangle "**Layer 5: Validation Layer** (Safety Net)" as L5 #FFEBEE {
  note right
    Post-processing checks catch anything
    that slips through other layers.
    ----
    //Check: Does output contain financial figures?//
    //  → If agent is Market Researcher, flag violation//
    //Check: Does output reference unauthorized data?//
    //  → Reject and re-prompt//
    ----
    **Enforcement:** Rule-based post-processing
    **Strength:** Safety net — catches edge cases
  end note
}

L1 -[hidden]down-> L2
L2 -[hidden]down-> L3
L3 -[hidden]down-> L4
L4 -[hidden]down-> L5

@enduml
